bond(uint256).details: The main bonding function: user deposits `paymentToken` (e.g., DAI, USDC, etc.) to receive RoboMoney at a discount.

params.tokenAmount: The amount of `paymentToken` the user is depositing.

checkContractRoboMoneyBalance().details: Check how many RoboMoney tokens the contract itself holds.

checkRoboMoneyBalance(address).details: Check the RoboMoney token balance of any user.

checkTokenAllowance(address).details: Check how much of the payment token (ERC20) the user has approved for this contract.

checkTokenBalance(address).details: Check the payment token (ERC20) balance of any user.

params._paymentToken: Address of the ERC20 token used for bonding (replaces WETH).
params._roboMoney: Address of the RoboMoney token (replaces mlAMPL).
params._targetPrice: “Base” price ratio for roboMoney vs. payment token.

withdraw(address,uint256,address).details: Owner can withdraw any ERC20 tokens (e.g. leftover paymentToken or minted RoboMoney).

params.recipient: Recipient address to receive the tokens.
params.token: Address of the ERC20 token to withdraw.
